"{\"uid\": \"tribuneindia.com-news-parisolympics2024-aman-sehrawat-cruzes-to-wrestling-bronze\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Rohit Mahajan in Paris    Aman Sehrawat, 21 years old, the future of wrestling, did what was expected of him today - he crushed Puerto Rico's Darian Toi Cruz 13-5 to earn India's fifth bronze of the Paris Olympics, the sixth medal overall.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 239, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17, \"end\": 22, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999986185742264, \"rank\": 1.3814277538969094e-06, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 128, \"end\": 139, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Puerto_Rico\", \"score\": 0.999400325562144, \"rank\": 0.0005397605347712386, \"text\": \"Puerto Rico\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Puerto_Rico\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Puerto_Rico\"}, {\"begin\": 171, \"end\": 176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.9977512470462953, \"rank\": 0.002236246566202724, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The night before, however, there was fear in the Indian camp - Sehrawat's weight had shot up to 62 kg through the day's three bouts, 5 kg above the limit of his weight class.\", \"from\": 243, \"to\": 417, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 292, \"end\": 303, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_Camp\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Indian camp\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_Camp\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_Camp\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I had to lose five kilos,\\\" said Sehrawat, blood on his face and sweat on his body, moments after his win.\", \"from\": 418, \"to\": 524, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I did not sleep the whole night...\", \"from\": 525, \"to\": 560, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I practised at night, too!\", \"from\": 561, \"to\": 587, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the morning, I was within the 57 kg limit!\\\"\", \"from\": 588, \"to\": 634, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sehrawat, the only man in the Indian squad, was unfazed by Cruz's early attacks.\", \"from\": 635, \"to\": 715, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 665, \"end\": 671, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_people\", \"score\": 0.9998897715847224, \"rank\": 0.00011023702388296106, \"text\": \"Indian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Puerto Rican grabbing his left leg; Sehrawat defended valiantly but conceded a point through a push-out.\", \"from\": 716, \"to\": 824, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 720, \"end\": 732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Puerto_Ricans\", \"score\": 0.996877850032995, \"rank\": 0.003129968996027964, \"text\": \"Puerto Rican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Puerto_Ricans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Puerto_Ricans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cruz again went for his legs, but now Sehrawat got hold of him and got two points - the Indian 2-1 up!\", \"from\": 825, \"to\": 927, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Cruz wasn't giving up, though; he grabbed Sehrawat's legs and twisted him - two points.\", \"from\": 931, \"to\": 1018, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sehrawat still had power and the strength of mind - he pushed Cruz out, and got two more points by taking him down.\", \"from\": 1019, \"to\": 1134, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Another takedown, another two points, and he led 6-3 at the hooter.\", \"from\": 1135, \"to\": 1202, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The second period was packed with action but less frenetic - Cruz seemed to be losing energy, Sehrawat drawing it from him.\", \"from\": 1204, \"to\": 1327, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After some good defence by the Puerto Rican, Sehrawat powered into him - another takedown, two more points, and the Jhajjar lad was in control at 8-5.\", \"from\": 1328, \"to\": 1478, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1359, \"end\": 1371, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Puerto_Ricans\", \"score\": 0.996877850032995, \"rank\": 0.003129968996027964, \"text\": \"Puerto Rican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Puerto_Ricans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Puerto_Ricans\"}, {\"begin\": 1444, \"end\": 1451, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jhajjar\", \"score\": 0.9999999979834229, \"rank\": 1.908660054198053e-09, \"text\": \"Jhajjar\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jhajjar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jhajjar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Desperate, Cruz had no option but to go for the Indian's legs and paid for the desperation - more points for Sehrawat, and a medal was a certainty at 13-5.\", \"from\": 1479, \"to\": 1634, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1527, \"end\": 1533, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_people\", \"score\": 0.9998897715847224, \"rank\": 0.00011023702388296106, \"text\": \"Indian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the end of it all, there was a bleeding wound on Sehrawat's face, but pride in his eyes.\", \"from\": 1638, \"to\": 1729, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Orphaned at 11, finding a second home at Delhi's Chhatrasal Stadium, the farmer's son from Jhajjar did what his idol Ravi Dahiya did at Tokyo 2020 - a medal in his very first Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 1730, \"to\": 1919, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1771, \"end\": 1776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Delhi\", \"score\": 0.999999993475285, \"rank\": 6.524799584323149e-09, \"text\": \"Delhi\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Delhi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Delhi\"}, {\"begin\": 1821, \"end\": 1828, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jhajjar\", \"score\": 0.9999999979834229, \"rank\": 1.908660054198053e-09, \"text\": \"Jhajjar\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jhajjar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jhajjar\"}, {\"begin\": 1847, \"end\": 1858, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ravi_Kumar_Dahiya\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ravi Dahiya\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ravi_Kumar_Dahiya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ravi_Kumar_Dahiya\"}, {\"begin\": 1866, \"end\": 1871, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9997290227882976, \"rank\": 0.0002684914029252482, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Take your experience further with Premium access.Thought-provoking Opinions, Expert Analysis, In-depth Insights and other Member Only Benefits  Already a Member?Sign In Now  The Tribune, now published from Chandigarh, started publication on February 2, 1881, in Lahore (now in Pakistan).\", \"from\": 1921, \"to\": 2208, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2127, \"end\": 2137, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chandigarh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0005501975521433e-19, \"text\": \"Chandigarh\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chandigarh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chandigarh\"}, {\"begin\": 2183, \"end\": 2189, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lahore\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.631856320944027e-14, \"text\": \"Lahore\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lahore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lahore\"}, {\"begin\": 2198, \"end\": 2206, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"score\": 0.9999991070353084, \"rank\": 8.7200455637411e-07, \"text\": \"Pakistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was started by Sardar Dyal Singh Majithia, a public-spirited philanthropist, and is run by a trust comprising five eminent persons as trustees.The Tribune, the largest selling English daily in North India, publishes news and views without any bias or prejudice of any kind.\", \"from\": 2209, \"to\": 2485, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2227, \"end\": 2233, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sardar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.458292865376454e-29, \"text\": \"Sardar\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sardar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sardar\"}, {\"begin\": 2234, \"end\": 2253, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dyal_Singh_Majithia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dyal Singh Majithia\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dyal_Singh_Majithia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dyal_Singh_Majithia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Restraint and moderation, rather than agitational language and partisanship, are the hallmarks of the newspaper.\", \"from\": 2486, \"to\": 2598, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is an independent newspaper in the real sense of the term.The Tribune has two sister publications, Punjabi Tribune (in Punjabi) and Dainik Tribune (in Hindi).\", \"from\": 2599, \"to\": 2760, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2701, \"end\": 2716, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjabi_Tribune\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Punjabi Tribune\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjabi_Tribune\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjabi_Tribune\"}, {\"begin\": 2721, \"end\": 2728, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjab\", \"score\": 0.9915121366524166, \"rank\": 0.008484111740503345, \"text\": \"Punjabi\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjab\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjab\"}, {\"begin\": 2734, \"end\": 2748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dainik_Tribune\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dainik Tribune\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dainik_Tribune\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dainik_Tribune\"}, {\"begin\": 2753, \"end\": 2758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hindi\", \"score\": 0.9999991389640014, \"rank\": 8.610314866289033e-07, \"text\": \"Hindi\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hindi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hindi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Remembering Sardar Dyal Singh Majithia\", \"from\": 2762, \"to\": 2800, \"entities\": []}]}"